Dear Luca

When you have no moderators the intercept applies everywhere. When you 
have moderators the intercept is the estimated value when all moderators 
take on the value zero, I think that may be what you are saying when you 
speak of 'low values'. It is always open to you to subtract a constant 
from moderators so that zero lies in the space of scientifically 
interesting values.

Michael

